<div id="sub-main" >
	<div id="wiki-content-block">

	
		


<div id="infobox" class="infobox"> 
 <div class="table-responsive"> 
  <table class="wiki_table"> 
   <tbody> 
    <tr> 
     <td style="text-align: center;"> <h3>Hawk Ring</h3> </td> 
    </tr> 
    <tr> 
     <td><img style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="/file/Dark-Souls-3/hawk_ring.png" alt="" width="100" height="131"></td> 
    </tr> 
    <tr> 
     <td><br> 
      <blockquote> 
       <p>Ring associated with Hawkeye Gough, one of the Four Knights of Gwyn, the First Lord.<br><br>Extends the range of arrows.<br><br>In his later years, the giant Gough was blinded, but this did not prevent him from striking down a calamitous dragon with his Greatbow.</p> 
      </blockquote> </td> 
    </tr> 
   </tbody> 
  </table> 
 </div> 
</div> 
<p><strong>Hawk Ring</strong> is a <a class="wiki_link" href="/Rings">Ring</a> in Dark Souls 3.</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 id="toc0" class="bonfire"><a name="x--item Usage"></a>Hawk Ring Effect</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Extends the range of <a class="wiki_link" title="Bows" href="/Bows">Bows</a> and <a class="wiki_link" title="Crossbows" href="/Crossbows">Crossbows</a>.</li> 
 <li>Reduces damage falloff&nbsp;of <a class="wiki_link" title="Throwing Knives" href="/Throwing+Knife">Throwing Knives</a>, <a class="wiki_link" title="Poison Throwing Knives" href="/Poison+Throwing+Knife">Poison Throwing Knives</a> and <a class="wiki_link" title="Kukris" href="/Kukri">Kukris</a>&nbsp;at long distances.</li> 
 <li>Raises the&nbsp;throwing arcs for <a class="wiki_link" title="Firebombs" href="/Firebomb">Firebombs</a>, <a class="wiki_link" title="Black Firebombs" href="/Black+Firebomb">Black Firebombs</a> and <a class="wiki_link" title="Lightning Urns" href="/Lightning+Urn">Lightning Urns</a> when used without lock-on.</li> 
 <li>Extends maximum zoom range of bows, crossbows, and binoculars (minimum zoom remains the same however, so seeing the effect requires further zooming with the directional pad)</li> 
 <li>Weight: 0.7</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 id="toc1" class="bonfire"><a name="x--item Locations"></a>Location</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Dropped by the bow-wielding&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" href="/Giant+of+the+Undead+Settlement">Giant</a>&nbsp;in the <a class="wiki_link" href="/Undead+Settlement">Undead Settlement</a>.</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">&nbsp;Videos</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li><a class="wiki_link" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xMtTkXlyOXk">Hawk Ring Location</a></li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 id="toc2" class="bonfire"><a name="x--Notes"></a>Notes and Trivia</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Extends effective range by 65%.</li> 
 <li>Projectiles have a gradual drop in performance the further you are away from the target. This ring will increase the distance before damage dropoff, which affects the trajectory and damage dealt with arrows and bolts when shot from far away.</li> 
 <li>Collect all seven <a class="wiki_link" title="Young White Branches" href="/Young+White+Branch">Young White Branches</a> at all three white birch trees, and the Giant will die, leaving the ring behind.</li> 
 <li>You can kill the Giant at any time to receive the ring.</li> 
 <li>At some point in the late game the Giant will die of natural cause. The player can go to the top of the tower and find the giant dead with the ring at his feet.</li> 
 <li>The "calamitous dragon" mentioned in the ring's description is <a class="wiki_link" title="Kalameet" href="https://darksouls.wiki.fextralife.com/Black+Dragon+Kalameet">Kalameet</a> from the <a class="wiki_link" title="Artorias of the Abyss" href="https://darksouls.wiki.fextralife.com/Artorias+of+the+Abyss+(Expansion)">Artorias of the Abyss</a> DLC for <a class="wiki_link" title="Dark Souls" href="https://darksouls.wiki.fextralife.com/About+Dark+Souls">Dark Souls</a>.</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
