				<li id="16015608" class="cmnt-root" data="11" data-d="1519874071000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t529923/Hawk-Ring" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">28 Feb 2018 22:14</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=165&p=16015608" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">I tested an Arbalest +10 (50 range) with Lloyd&apos;s ring and Hawk ring with the hollows on Cementery of Ash bonefire, as they don&apos;t have armor:<br/>Sniper Bolts with both rings does 334 dmg to both hollows (at auto-lock distance and aiming the fartest hollow from the red mark on the floor)<br/>Heavy Bolts with both rings does 349 at auto lock distance and 306 aiming from the same spot<br/>WITHOUT HAWK RING:(but with Lloyd&apos;s)<br/>Sniper bolt does 334/276<br/>Heavy Bolt does 349/200<br/><br/>Conclusion: Sniper bolts almost ignore the damage drop-off using Hawk&apos;s, besides that, the base damage is the same at Lock-on distance with ring or not.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16015608" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16015608" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">0</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>12</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section cl